CommonFields.Title: Viscoelastic properties and thermal degradation kinetics of silica/PMMA nanocomposites
Author: Hu, Yu-Hsiang
Chen, Chuh-Yung
Wang, Cheng-Chien
CommonFields.Location: Department of Chemical Engineering, National Cheng-Kung University, Tainan 70101, Taiwan

ChooseParameter.Other: Methyl methacrylate (MMA) was distillated twice before being used.

Filler.Description: Methyl (-CH3) and ethylene (-CH2-) groups (2862 cm^-1 - 2963 cm^-1) are present in the modified silica.

Mixing.Description: The silica powder was well dispersed throughout the MMA monomer under sonification to yield various concentrations of silica/MMA solution.
The different concentrations of silica/MMA solution (100 g) with 0.7 g AIBN were placed in a 200 ml beaker.  This mixture was stirred at room temperature under flowing nitrogen.

Fourier_Transform_Infrared_Spectroscopy.Description: FT-IR, was conducted using a BIO-RAD FTS-40A + UMA500 spectrometer with KBr pellet at 4 cm^-1 resolution.

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description: Samples of approximately 10e15 mg were heated at various heating rates under nitrogen purge (70 ml/min). Isothermal TGA was carried out by heating the sample to 220 (C for 2 h under nitrogen purge.
